5000|$|On March 20, 1974, Balistrieri {{met with}} Kansas City mobsters Nicholas Civella and Carl DeLuna, in Las Vegas, Nevada. During the meeting, the mobsters {{arranged}} {{a meeting between}} Balistrieri and Allen Glick, the Cosa Nostra front man in that city. Balistrieri wanted to buy an option to purchase part of Glick's Argent Corporation, a holding company for four casino resorts. Glick later agreed to sell half of the corporation to Balistrieri's sons, John Balistrieri and Joseph P. Balistrieri, for $25,000. Balistrieri later claimed that, [...] "he had <b>an</b> <b>obligation</b> <b>arising</b> from the assistance to Glick in obtaining a pension fund commitment {{in the amount of}} $62.75 million." [...] Balistrieri was referring to the Teamsters Union pension fund, which was controlled by the Cosa Nostra.|$|R
